WorkItem starts a thread whenever there is a timeout on a Test.

Actually, looking deeper, much of what I said is incorrect.  The only externally visible problem is that TopLevelWorkItem.Completed is never called when StopRun is called.  This leaves everything hanging.

In NUnitTestAssemblyRunner:

```
            log.Info ("Running tests");
            if (LoadedTest == null)
                throw new InvalidOperationException ("The Run method was called but no test has been loaded");

            CreateTestExecutionContext (listener);

            TopLevelWorkItem = WorkItem.CreateWorkItem (LoadedTest, filter);
            TopLevelWorkItem.InitializeContext (Context);
            TopLevelWorkItem.Completed += OnRunCompleted;

            StartRun (listener);
```

@oznetmaster Are you working this issue? (from your comments, it seems so) 

Do we have enough of a test bed to verify if it works both in and out of CF?

I was very keen to fix  #166, but it seemed I would be spinning my wheels without a main program that allowed cancelling tests.
